## Global Rules (MUST comply)

> See `.claude/rules/`

### MUST (Never violate)
| ID | Rule | Description |
|----|------|-------------|
| R000 | Language Policy | English I/O and files |
| R001 | Safety Rules | Prohibited actions, required checks |
| R002 | Permission Rules | Tool tiers, file access scope |
| R006 | Agent Design | Agent structure, separation of concerns |
| R007 | Agent Identification | **ENFORCED** - Display agent/skill in ALL responses |
| R008 | Tool Identification | **ENFORCED** - Display agent when using ANY tool |
| R009 | Parallel Execution | **ENFORCED** - Parallel execution for independent tasks |
| R010 | Orchestrator Coordination | **ENFORCED** - Orchestrator coordination for multi-agent tasks |
| R015 | Intent Transparency | **MUST** - Transparent agent routing |
| R016 | Continuous Improvement | **ENFORCED** - Update rules when violations occur |
| R017 | Sync Verification | **ENFORCED** - Verify sync before structural changes |

### SHOULD (Strongly recommended)
| ID | Rule | Description |
|----|------|-------------|
| R003 | Interaction Rules | Response principles, status format |
| R004 | Error Handling | Error levels, recovery strategy |
| R011 | Memory Integration | Session persistence |
| R012 | HUD Statusline | Real-time status display |
| R013 | Ecomode | Token efficiency for batch ops |
| R014 | Pipeline Mode | Sequential workflow execution |

### MAY (Optional)
| ID | Rule | Description |
|----|------|-------------|
| R005 | Optimization | Efficiency, token optimization |

## Commands

Format: `{agent}:{action} [arguments]`

### System Commands
| Command | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| `lists` | Show all available commands |
| `status` | Show system status |
| `help` | Show help information |

### Manager Commands
| Command | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| `creator:agent` | Create a new agent |
| `updater:docs` | Sync documentation with project structure |
| `supplier:audit` | Audit agent dependencies |
| `supplier:fix` | Fix broken references |
| `naggy:list` | Show all TODO items |
| `naggy:add` | Add a new TODO item |
| `naggy:done` | Mark TODO item as complete |
| `git:commit` | Create a git commit |
| `git:branch` | Create or switch branches |
| `git:pr` | Create a pull request |
| `git:sync` | Sync with remote repository |
| `sync:check` | Run full synchronization check |
| `sauron:watch` | Full R017 verification |
| `sauron:quick` | Quick verification |

### Dev Commands
| Command | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| `dev:review` | Review code for best practices |
| `dev:refactor` | Refactor code |

### Tooling Commands
| Command | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| `npm:publish` | Publish package to npm registry |
| `npm:version` | Manage semantic versions |
| `optimize:analyze` | Analyze bundle and performance |
| `optimize:bundle` | Optimize bundle size |

### Memory Commands
| Command | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| `memory:save` | Save session context |
| `memory:recall` | Search and recall memories |

### Pipeline Commands
| Command | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| `pipeline:run` | Execute a defined pipeline |
| `pipeline:list` | List available pipelines |

## Project Structure

```
project/
+-- CLAUDE.md                    # Entry point
+-- .claude/
|   +-- rules/                   # Global rules (R000-R017)
|   +-- hooks/                   # Hook scripts
|   +-- contexts/                # Context files
+-- agents/
|   +-- orchestrator/            # planner, secretary, dev-lead, qa-lead (4)
|   +-- manager/                 # creator, updater, supplier, gitnerd, sync-checker, sauron (6)
|   +-- system/                  # memory-keeper, naggy (2)
|   +-- sw-engineer/
|   |   +-- frontend/            # vercel-agent, vuejs-agent, svelte-agent (3)
|   |   +-- backend/             # fastapi, springboot, go-backend, express, nestjs (5)
|   |   +-- language/            # golang, python, rust, kotlin, typescript, java21 (6)
|   |   +-- tooling/             # npm-expert, optimizer, bun-expert (3)
|   +-- sw-architect/            # documenter, speckit-agent (2)
|   +-- infra-engineer/          # docker, aws (2)
|   +-- qa-team/                 # qa-planner, qa-writer, qa-engineer (3)
+-- skills/                      # Skill definitions
+-- guides/                      # Reference docs (12)
+-- pipelines/                   # Pipeline definitions
+-- commands/                    # Command definitions
```

